/", "experiences/4/jobEndedOn": "9-2016", "experiences/4/jobLocation": "Phuket, Thailand", "experiences/4/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/4/jobStartedOn": "10-2015", "experiences/4/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/4/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D0BAQFYYdJOlpzC7g/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1720426207831?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=NVWT7vAaSts8Ux-3OLXv_uoFGyGQfo7rUFvNjrI0lMY", "experiences/4/title": "General Manager (Swissotel Resort Phuket)", "experiences/5/companyId": "2449", "experiences/5/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/5/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/hilton/", "experiences/5/companyName": "Hilton Worldwide", "experiences/5/companySize": "10001-0", "experiences/5/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:2449", "experiences/5/companyWebsite": "http://stories.hilton.com", "experiences/5/jobEndedOn": "10-2015", "experiences/5/jobLocation": "Hua Hin, Thailand", "experiences/5/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/5/jobStartedOn": "7-2015", "experiences/5/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/5/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQGaUrNbmNf_sg/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1726853193572/hilton_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=iB1JGDdV-yJUje-GRQZx89ratKm7W7S0bKYqWhxOVZQ", "experiences/5/title": "Acting General Manager (Hilton Hua Hin Resort & Spa)", "experiences/6/companyId": "2449", "experiences/6/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/6/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/hilton/", "experiences/6/companyName": "Hilton Worldwide", "experiences/6/companySize": "10001-0", "experiences/6/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:2449", "experiences/6/companyWebsite": "http://stories.hilton.com", "experiences/6/jobDescription": "• Actively communicate with and support the General Manager, Operational Departments, Human Resources and Sales & Marketing Teams to ensure flawless execution of service standards and implementation of resort wide initiatives\n• Active member of the resort Executive Committee\n• Assume responsibilities of the General Manager in his absence\n• Openly communicate with resort owners and regional team on all relevant resort matters\n• Direct and lead the Rooms, Food & Beverage, Engineering, Security, Spa & Recreation\n• Responsible for budgets and forecasting\n• Develop and lead resort management team to promote healthy turnover within the company\n• Work with resort’s key stakeholder to maximize owner profits\n\nAlong with the day to day duties of directing and coordinating the Rooms, Food & Beverage and Minor Operating Departments in the resort, my role as Director of Operations includes setting and maintaining 5 star service standards throughout the resort, implementing strategies to drive profit and achieve optimum flow through and ensuring efficient operation of the business.", "experiences/6/jobEndedOn": "7-2015", "experiences/6/jobLocation": "Hua Hin, Thailand", "experiences/6/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/6/jobStartedOn": "5-2014", "experiences/6/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/6/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQGaUrNbmNf_sg/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1726853193572/hilton_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=iB1JGDdV-yJUje-GRQZx89ratKm7W7S0bKYqWhxOVZQ", "experiences/6/title": "Director of Operations (Hilton Hua Hin Resort & Spa)", "experiences/7/companyId": "3035", "experiences/7/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/7/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/shrw/", "experiences/7/companyName": "Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide, Inc.", "experiences/7/companySize": "10001-0", "experiences/7/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:3035", "experiences/7/companyWebsite": "https://www.marriott.com", "experiences/7/jobDescription": "• Communicate with and support the GM, Ops, HR and S&M Teams to ensure flawless execution of service standards and implementation of resort initiatives\n• Executive Committee Member\n• Assume responsibilities of the GM in his absence\n• Communicate with owners & regional team on all relevant matters\n• Work with key stakeholder to maximize profits\n\nAlong with the day to day duties of directing the Rooms, F&B & MODs in the resort, my role as Ops Manager includes setting and maintaining 5 star standards, implementing strategies to drive profit and ensure efficient operation of the hotel.  In 2012 I was successful in driving improvement in the rooms department productivity 9%.  In F&B, I implemented strategies that improved productivity 8% resulting in IRD profit 6% YOY, Pool Bar profit 8% YOY, Lobby Bar profit 6% YOY and BQT profit 4% YOY.  \n\nAs Ops Manager I have been successful in positioning the resort to achieve best in class results for guest satisfaction, guest loyalty program goals and quality assurance mystery audits.  In 2012 my hotel was recognized in the following guest experience metrics against the 14 Starwood hotels in the Pacific:\n\t\n1 of 14 SPG Program Guest Acknowledgement\n1 of 14 Front Desk Staff Helpful\n2 of 14 In Room Dining Experience\n3 of 14 Bar Experience  \n\nIn Q1 2013, the resort commenced a $10M AUD renovation of the guest rooms, corridors, façade, restaurant and bar which included rebranding and partnering with a 3rd party celebrity chef, Peter Kuruvita. Throughout this project, I have been a key stakeholder for both the rooms and restaurant rollout.  From conceptualization and development of the concept to execution of Noosa Beach House Peter Kuruvita, I have been instrumental in the planning, consultation, procurement and development as well as implementation of operating procedures.  The new room product has been well received by our guests and Noosa Beach House has opened to rave reviews.", "experiences/7/jobEndedOn": "12-2013", "experiences/7/jobLocation": "Noosa Heads, QLD", "experiences/7/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/7/jobStartedOn": "3-2012", "experiences/7/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/7/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFpl2hTC-Im0Q/company-logo_400_400/B56ZeDjFZOGQAo-/0/1750258702517/shrw_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=taP0edqTnsdYP7ZRs2Z_0AP7mnMvD7r8TVgGzsW-QHo", "experiences/7/title": "Hotel Operations Manager (Sheraton Noosa Resort & Spa)", "experiences/8/companyId": "3035", "experiences/8/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/8/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/shrw/", "experiences/8/companyName": "Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide, Inc.", "experiences/8/companySize": "10001-0", "experiences/8/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:3035", "experiences/8/companyWebsite": "https://www.marriott.com", "experiences/8/jobDescription": "• Actively communicated with and supported the General Manager, Operational Departments, Human Resources and Sales & Marketing Teams to ensure flawless execution of service standards and implementation of resort wide initiatives\n• Led, directed and coordinated the Rooms Department in the resort\n• Developed the management team to promote healthy turnover within the company\n• Strategically managed and led the Rooms Department to exceed resort goals and achieve best in class results\n• Maintained all financial aspects of department which included developing budgets, forecasting, labor productivity, inventory, payroll, purchase orders and controls for cash handling\n• Implement systems, programs, initiative and procedures to drive efficiency, productivity and enhance the guest experience\n\nAs Front Office Manager, I oversaw and managed the day to day operations of the rooms department in the resort.  Through strategic management and streamlining processes and procedures I successfully improved Front Office productivity by 15% over a 2 year period.  In addition, I introduced and implemented an upselling program that tripled year on year results.  \nAs Front Office Manager, I successfully positioned the resort to achieve best in class results for guest satisfaction, guest loyalty program goals and associate satisfaction results.  An example of this includes increasing guest loyalty program success rates from 36% to 68% over a 12 month period.\n\nGiven my performance in this position, I was nominated by the resort Executive Committee to be accepted into the Starwood High Potential Executive Committee Program.  The screening process involved psychometric testing and in depth screening and interviews.  I was accepted into the program as 1 of 10 candidates by the Starwood Pacific Regional Team and successfully graduated from the program.", "experiences/8/jobEndedOn": "3-2012", "experiences/8/jobLocation": "Noosa Heads, QLD", "experiences/8/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/8/jobStartedOn": "1-2011", "experiences/8/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/8/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFpl2hTC-Im0Q/company-logo_400_400/B56ZeDjFZOGQAo-/0/1750258702517/shrw_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=taP0edqTnsdYP7ZRs2Z_0AP7mnMvD7r8TVgGzsW-QHo", "experiences/8/title": "Front Office Manager (Sheraton Noosa Resort & Spa)", "experiences/9/companyId": "3035", "experiences/9/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/9/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/shrw/", "experiences/9/companyName": "Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide, Inc.", "experiences/9/companySize": "10001-0", "experiences/9/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:3035", "experiences/9/companyWebsite": "https://www.marriott.com", "experiences/9/jobDescription": "• Managed Welcome Office staff including W Insiders, WD Agents, Welcome Ambassadors, Concierges, and Whatever/Whenever Agents\n• Maintained all financial aspects of the department including productivity, inventory, payroll, PO's and controls of cash handling\n• Actively trained and developed staff to ensure flawless execution of hotel policies, procedures, and service standards\n• Piloted Make a Green Choice program for W Hotels and Resorts NAD\n• Acting Director of WO during transition period of department\n• F&B Manager during transition period of F&B department\n\nAs WD Manager, I oversaw and managed the day to day ops in the WO while working directly with the Style (HSK).  While managing the day to day WO ops there was also a component of managing the F&B venues.  In this position, I successfully implemented strategies that significantly improved guest satisfaction and guest loyalty program goals, ultimately being recognized as a best in class performer in W Hotels NAD.  This increase included improving guest loyalty program success rates from 37% to 47% in 12 months, achieving the highest success rate of 7 area hotels.  \n\nWhile at the W SF I piloted the “Make a Green Choice Program” for the W Hotels NAD which included trialing different delivery methods and recommending the best approach to the brand team that aligned with W Hotels while achieving high participation rates.  Throughout this process I worked with the Area Director of Six Sigma and ultimately the program trialed and developed was accepted and implemented in W Hotels NAD.\n\nIn Q1 and Q2 2010, I assumed the position of Director of WO during a restructuring period of the Rooms Department.  \n\nIn Q3 2010, I was made responsible for the position of F&B Outlets Manager for XYZ Restaurant, XYZ Bar and the W Lounge.  This included overseeing breakfast, lunch, dinner, bar and lounge service, opening and closing the F&B venues and ensuring execution of flawless customer service.", "experiences/9/jobEndedOn": "12-2010", "experiences/9/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/9/jobStartedOn": "1-2009", "experiences/9/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/9/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQFpl2hTC-Im0Q/company-logo_400_400/B56ZeDjFZOGQAo-/0/1750258702517/shrw_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=taP0edqTnsdYP7ZRs2Z_0AP7mnMvD7r8TVgGzsW-QHo", "experiences/9/title": "Welcome Desk Manager (Front Desk Manager, W San Francisco)", "experiences/10/companyId": "3035", "experiences/10/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/10/companyLink1": "h